## Installation Instructions

===================
System Requirements
===================

SNP Conversion and Genotype Concordance have been developed and tested with
Python version 3.6.3. They are not compatible with Python2. Python 3 must be
installed to use these programs.

============
Installation
============

**NOTE:** This program can be used on Unix-based operating systems (Mac OSX,
Linux) and on Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL). Use within Windows itself is
not supported.

There are no special installation instructions for SNP Conversion and Genotype
Concordance programs. All required dependencies can be installed using the [pip
package installer for python](https://pypi.org/project/pip/).

Download the program from Github or clone it into your directory. To download
all dependencies, install the SNP Conversion wheel with

`pip3 install dist/SNP_Conversion-2.0-py3-none-any.whl`

Use the `--user` flag for a local install.


If you already have all the required dependencies listed below, you can simply
run SNP Conversion or Genome Concordance with

`./snp_conversion` or `./genotype_concordance`



==================
Required Libraries
==================

SNP Conversion and Genotype Concordance require the following non-standard
libraries:

 - pandas
 - numpy
 - toolz

Genotype Concordance requires the following additional non-standard libraries:

 - scikit-allel

Non-standard libraries can be installed with pip3:

`pip3 install [library]`

Or conda:

`conda install -c conda-forge [library]`


The following standard libraries are required by both programs:

 - os
 - atexit
 - warnings
 - argparse
 - sys
 - time
 - functools
 - platform
 - concurrent.futures
 - zipfile
 - gzip
 - bz2
 - io
 - collections
